    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-28T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="678"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-28T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 28, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 28—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. Department’s 137, May 23, 2 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d678fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> Ringwalt reports May 27, 11 a.m., that all American citizens
                    had returned to Yunnanfu by May 12th.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
